.git
.github
bin
deploy
docs
migrations
# SIN-63332 — re-include the migrations/ tree in the build context so the
# crm-server runtime stage can ship the .sql files at /migrations. The
# `cd-stg` workflow's `migrate-up` step (stg-deploy.sh `migrate-up` verb)
# extracts /migrations from the just-deployed image with `docker cp` and
# mounts it into a one-shot `migrate/migrate` sidecar. This lets the
# pipeline apply DB schema changes between deploy and login smoke without
# needing a separate scp of migrations to the VPS each release. The bytes
# are static SQL (~60 KB) and the runtime user (UID 65532 nonroot) only
# reads them; nothing under `migrations/` is executable at runtime.
!migrations
scripts
!scripts/backup.sh
!scripts/backup-restore.sh
tools
web
# SIN-63299 — keep the whole web/static/ runtime asset tree in the build
# context. cmd/server/customdomain_wire.go mounts a FileServer on
# `web/static/` and templates reference /static/css/*.css,
# /static/js/*.js, /static/customdomain.css and /static/customdomain.js
# from real production pages. The previous `!web/static/vendor`-only
# exception was tight enough to bring in CHECKSUMS.txt (imported via
# go:embed) but left every other asset off the runtime image, so the
# FileServer 404'd them in staging/prod (auth.css, privacy.css,
# customdomain.css visibly broke /login after SIN-63294). Re-include the
# tree as a whole; there is nothing under web/static/ that is not
# runtime-served.
!web/static
*.md
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
